As shown in Table 1, many clean energy production technologies require several energy-critical elements, which are listed with their extensive uses in the table (Price 2011; Hurd et al. 2012; Dutta et al. 2016). Nevertheless, it should be noted that this list of energy-critical elements for a truly green future is not exhaustive. The use of these elements is essential to the development of many high-tech devices today.Table 1
